.TH TVDINNER 1 "July 2026" "tvdinner 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
tvdinner \- play IPTV streams from an M3U playlist, with XMLTV EPG overlay and guide
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tvdinner
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fIURL\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B tvdinner
plays IPTV streams from an M3U/M3U8 playlist (or a direct video/audio stream
URL) using mpv. \fIURL\fR may be an http(s) URL or a local file path.
.PP
If \fIURL\fR looks like an M3U playlist, playback starts on the channel
given by \fB\-\-channel\fR, or the first channel in the playlist otherwise
(use the program guide's channel switching, see KEYS, to change channel
without restarting). Otherwise \fIURL\fR is played directly as a stream.
.PP
EPG (electronic programme guide) data is drawn automatically from the
playlist's own embedded XMLTV reference where available, or from an
explicit \fB\-\-epg\fR URL. EPG times are timezone-aware and can be
corrected with \fB\-\-time-shift\fR for feeds that report incorrect times.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Show a help message and exit.
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-channel\fR \fICHANNEL\fR
Channel name (or 1-based index) to play; defaults to the first channel
in the playlist.
.TP
\fB\-\-list\fR
List channels in the playlist and exit without playing.
.TP
\fB\-\-epg\fR \fIURL\fR
XMLTV EPG URL or local file, overriding any EPG source discovered in the
M3U playlist.
.TP
\fB\-\-tz\fR \fINAME\fR
IANA timezone for displaying EPG times, e.g. \fIEurope/London\fR (default:
system local timezone).
.TP
\fB\-\-time\-shift\fR \fISHIFT\fR
Correct EPG feed clock errors, e.g. \fI+1h\fR, \fI\-30m\fR, or minutes as a
plain integer. Applies to any channel without its own override in
\fB\-\-epg\-shifts\fR.
.TP
\fB\-\-epg\-shifts\fR \fIPATH\fR
JSON file mapping a channel's display name (as shown by \fB\-\-list\fR) to
a per-channel EPG time-shift override, for feeds where different channels
are off by different amounts, e.g.:
.RS
.nf
{"BBC One": "+1h", "TCM US West": "-3h"}
.fi
.RE
Keyed by display name rather than tvg_id, since real-world playlists
commonly have several distinct channels (e.g. an East/West regional pair)
sharing one tvg_id for EPG mapping, which a tvg_id-keyed override couldn't
tell apart.
.PP
Default: \fI~/.config/tvdinner/epg_shifts.json\fR. A missing file is not
an error; malformed entries are reported as warnings and skipped rather
than preventing startup. Can also be adjusted live with the \fB[\fR /
\fB]\fR guide keybinding, see KEYS.
.SH KEYS
While a stream is playing, in addition to mpv's own default key bindings:
.TP
.B i
Show the current/next programme info overlay, including video/audio
quality badges (resolution, codecs, fps, HDR, channel layout); while the
program guide is open, shows full details for the selected guide
programme instead.
.TP
.B g
Toggle the full program guide.
.TP
.B LEFT / RIGHT
Page the program guide's timeline back/forward by 30 minutes (guide only;
otherwise these seek the video as usual).
.TP
.B UP / DOWN
Move the program guide's channel selection cursor (guide only).
.TP
.B PGUP / PGDWN
Move the program guide's channel selection cursor a full page at a time
(guide only; otherwise these seek the video as usual).
.TP
.B ENTER
Switch to the selected guide channel and close the guide; while typing a
filter query (see \fBf\fR below), confirms it instead.
.TP
.B [ / ]
Nudge the selected guide channel's EPG shift back/forward by 1 minute,
saving the change to \fB\-\-epg\-shifts\fR immediately (guide only).
.TP
.B f
Open a text-entry dialog to filter the program guide's channel list by
name (case-insensitive substring match); ENTER applies it, ESC cancels
(guide only).
.TP
.B c
Clear any active guide filter and show every channel again (guide only).
.TP
.B ESC
Close the programme details popup, or cancel an in-progress guide filter
query.
.TP
.B z
Cycle the video's display aspect ratio (Auto, 4:3, 16:9, 2.35:1, 1:1).
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
List the channels in a playlist:
.B tvdinner https://example.com/playlist.m3u \-\-list
.TP
Play a channel directly by name:
.B tvdinner playlist.m3u \-\-channel "BBC One"
.TP
Play a direct stream URL:
.B tvdinner https://example.com/stream.m3u8
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR mpv (1)
